00:46:09.450 --> 00:46:12.120
biased in the way we perceive
it isn't this

00:46:12.120 --> 00:46:13.170
differential argument.

00:46:13.170 --> 00:46:15.660
It's this argument about
ensembles and entropy and

00:46:15.660 --> 00:46:16.290
stuff like that.

00:46:16.290 --> 00:46:20.740
So to me, those two thoughts in
my head are not reconciled

00:46:20.740 --> 00:46:22.140
in any constructive way.

00:46:22.140 --> 00:46:23.930
So could you elaborate
on the relationship

00:46:23.930 --> 00:46:24.860
between those two?

00:46:24.860 --> 00:46:25.230
DAVE GOLDBERG: Right.

00:46:25.230 --> 00:46:31.470
So yeah, I tried to take entire
of Chapter Two of my

00:46:31.470 --> 00:46:35.070
book and brush it into about 30
seconds of exposition here.

00:46:35.070 --> 00:46:37.890
So it's a fair question.

00:46:37.890 --> 00:46:41.640
So the issue is we've got
two different senses--

00:46:41.640 --> 00:46:43.430
at least two different
philosophers would probably

00:46:43.430 --> 00:46:45.230
give several more of
the arrow of time.

00:46:45.230 --> 00:46:46.100
One, you could call
it, almost, a

00:46:46.100 --> 00:46:47.840
psychological arrow, right?

00:46:47.840 --> 00:46:49.680
The remembering the past
and not the future.

00:46:49.680 --> 00:46:56.050
You've got an entropy arrow,
which is the increase in

00:46:56.050 --> 00:46:58.870
entropy goes toward
the future.

00:46:58.870 --> 00:47:00.790
We've also got an
arrow of time--

00:47:00.790 --> 00:47:03.490
at least in the equations, where
we're implying them-- in

00:47:03.490 --> 00:47:04.180
the weak force.

00:47:04.180 --> 00:47:08.025
Because we say the arrow goes
this way, and that's the one

00:47:08.025 --> 00:47:12.810
that defines how matter
works, and so on.

00:47:12.810 --> 00:47:14.725
And so part of the problem--

00:47:17.490 --> 00:47:21.000
and this is something I try
to approach in the book by

00:47:21.000 --> 00:47:22.880
getting humans out of the
equation entirely.

00:47:22.880 --> 00:47:24.520
Like we don't know
how brains work.

00:47:24.520 --> 00:47:29.180
But thinking about how a robot
or a disk drive or something

00:47:29.180 --> 00:47:30.640
like that would work.

00:47:30.640 --> 00:47:32.190
And you're a robot.

00:47:32.190 --> 00:47:33.100
You're awoken.

00:47:33.100 --> 00:47:36.920
You look at your disk.

00:47:36.920 --> 00:47:39.590
And you do not know--

00:47:39.590 --> 00:47:41.050
I mean, this is not about
the arrow of time.

00:47:41.050 --> 00:47:42.960
This is just sort of about
the relationship between

00:47:42.960 --> 00:47:46.090
information and entropy
and memories.

00:47:46.090 --> 00:47:48.850
You look at your disk, and
you see that all of your

00:47:48.850 --> 00:47:52.190
bits are set to 0.

00:47:52.190 --> 00:47:55.470
And you say, OK, this
is a clean slate.

00:47:55.470 --> 00:47:56.860
I am--

00:47:56.860 --> 00:47:58.904
I have no memories.

00:47:58.904 --> 00:48:02.030
On the other hand, I wake you
up as a robot, and there is

00:48:02.030 --> 00:48:04.360
this pattern of zeros
and ones.

00:48:04.360 --> 00:48:06.470
A complicated pattern,
not 0101.

00:48:06.470 --> 00:48:10.080
Some complicated thing that
you can't figure out,

00:48:10.080 --> 00:48:12.260
necessarily, what it means.

00:48:12.260 --> 00:48:14.070
You don't know anything else.

00:48:14.070 --> 00:48:17.060
The question is, are those
legitimate memories, or is

00:48:17.060 --> 00:48:18.310
that noise?

00:48:21.140 --> 00:48:24.710
And this is something we have
no great reconciliation to.

00:48:24.710 --> 00:48:27.810
Because our universe did start
with low entropy, and yet

00:48:27.810 --> 00:48:33.060
there's no physical principle
that says why that should be.

00:48:33.060 --> 00:48:35.190
And so the assumption is either
there's a physical

00:48:35.190 --> 00:48:43.720
principle we don't know, or
there are two states of the

00:48:43.720 --> 00:48:47.230
universe, one at low entropy and
one at high entropy, and

00:48:47.230 --> 00:48:50.590
there is another physical
principle that basically says

00:48:50.590 --> 00:48:53.220
the arrow of time is, by
definition, moving from the

00:48:53.220 --> 00:48:53.850
low to the high.

00:48:53.850 --> 00:48:57.850
Now I'll tell you what my
problem with that is, the sort

00:48:57.850 --> 00:49:00.120
of entropy making time.

00:49:00.120 --> 00:49:05.110
It is almost impossible to ever
describe a single state

00:49:05.110 --> 00:49:06.390
of the universe.

00:49:06.390 --> 00:49:08.180
I mean, because the universe is
not causally connected at

00:49:08.180 --> 00:49:09.470
any point to one another.

00:49:09.470 --> 00:49:14.310
So saying "The universe is
increasing in entropy" is an

00:49:14.310 --> 00:49:16.580
almost meaningless statement,
because there's no process by

00:49:16.580 --> 00:49:19.530
which something over the
entire universe can be

00:49:19.530 --> 00:49:22.930
integrated and calculated.

00:49:22.930 --> 00:49:26.090
So the fact that the whole
universe, or some part of the

00:49:26.090 --> 00:49:30.350
multiverse, which is now not
causally connected to one

00:49:30.350 --> 00:49:33.220
another, where some property
defined over that entire

00:49:33.220 --> 00:49:36.390
region then defines the arrow
of time, I don't see any

00:49:36.390 --> 00:49:38.670
mechanism for how
that could work.

00:49:38.670 --> 00:49:48.370
So it is absolutely an open
question, as to why the one

00:49:48.370 --> 00:49:50.740
should be related
to the other.

00:49:50.740 --> 00:49:57.910
The fact that time exists as a
dimension that behaves very,

00:49:57.910 --> 00:50:00.150
very different from space--

00:50:00.150 --> 00:50:04.030
like one could almost an
anthropic argument about that.

00:50:04.030 --> 00:50:05.900
So time does behave differently
from space.

00:50:05.900 --> 00:50:08.480
Regardless of which direction
the arrow of time is, the fact

00:50:08.480 --> 00:50:12.560
that there is dimension means
that we can do things like

00:50:12.560 --> 00:50:19.780
learn from the past, and make
inferences, and so on.

00:50:19.780 --> 00:50:22.660
Which we would not be able to do
in quite the same way if we

00:50:22.660 --> 00:50:24.860
lived in, say, four dimensions
in space with a universe with

00:50:24.860 --> 00:50:26.460
no time at all.

00:50:29.610 --> 00:50:31.840
And it may be that
there are part--

00:50:31.840 --> 00:50:32.950
if you believe in
the multiverse--

00:50:32.950 --> 00:50:34.440
there are parts of the
multiverse with different

00:50:34.440 --> 00:50:37.460
dimensionality, and we are
simply here because this is

00:50:37.460 --> 00:50:40.770
the most complicated one that
is anthropically favorable,

00:50:40.770 --> 00:50:45.020
such that we would be able to
exist at all, or anything

00:50:45.020 --> 00:50:46.550
would be able to exist at all.

00:50:46.550 --> 00:50:50.165
So I fully recognize I've given
you a non-answer, but

00:50:50.165 --> 00:50:52.900
I've hopefully sort of at least
laid out the space of

00:50:52.900 --> 00:50:55.282
the problem.

00:50:55.282 --> 00:50:55.720
Yes?

